
{center}
{subhead} Amiga Auctions press release{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

{bold}FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE{nobold}
{p} {p}
Toronto, March 20, 1999: clickBOOM announces a fully automatic real-time 
online Auction place now open to all Amiga users.
{p} {p}
After a month of successful operation at The Portal and due to a high 
demand, clickBOOM has taken the next step, making Amiga Auctions available 
to everyone.
{p} {p}
This is where all the action is -- you can bid on or sell Amiga-related 
items at the one and only place of its kind on Amiga.  Finally there is a 
place for Amiga users to be able to trade their hardware in a simple and 
absolutely private manner.
{p} {p}
1. Amiga Auctions is the place where you will find the best Amiga deals, 
guaranteed.
{p} {p}
2. Bidding is absolutely free.
{p} {p}
3. If you have an Amiga-related item to sell, Amiga Auctions is the place - 
hold an auction and have other Amiga users bid on it.  It's fully automatic 
- create a new auction in less than 5 minutes, and don't worry about it 
until you make a sale at the highest offered price.  Best of all, it's free 
if your item doesn't sell!
{p} {p}
4. Advanced options such as Automatic Bidder, three types of Auctions, 
notification, etc.
{p} {p}
5. English and German, with more languages coming soon.
{p} {p}
To see all of the Auctions just visit {link http://clickboom.com/auctions}http://clickboom.com/auctions{end}
{p} {p}
If you wish to bid on, or sell items, fill out a simple form to register 
yourself, and you will automatically receive access within seconds.
{p} {p}
Portal users should continue accessing Auctions through The Portal.
{p} {p}
Best regards,{p}
clickBOOM
